    "## a. Analyzing Article Distribution over Time: \n",
    "### Extracting the year and month from the date column and creating visualizations to see how the number of articles varies over different time periods.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "fac3372c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert Published Date to datetime format\n",
    "df['Published Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Published Date'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract year and month from Published Date\n",
    "df['Year'] = df['Published Date'].dt.year\n",
    "df['Month'] = df['Published Date'].dt.month\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the number of articles by year\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.countplot(x='Year', data=df)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Year')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Articles')\n",
    "plt.title('Article Distribution by Year')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the number of articles by month\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.countplot(x='Month', data=df)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Month')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Articles')\n",
    "plt.title('Article Distribution by Month')\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]

    "from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize\n",
    "from nltk.corpus import stopwords\n",
    "from wordcloud import WordCloud\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tokenize the article text\n",
    "df['Tokenized Text'] = df['Article Text'].apply(word_tokenize)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove stopwords\n",
    "stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))\n",
    "df['Filtered Text'] = df['Tokenized Text'].apply(lambda x: [word for word in x if word.lower() not in stop_words])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Flatten the list of filtered words\n",
    "filtered_words = [word for sublist in df['Filtered Text'] for word in sublist]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate word cloud\n",
    "wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white').generate(' '.join(filtered_words))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the word cloud\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.title('Common Keywords in Articles')\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# 2. Text Preprocessing: \n",
    "\n",
    "### Preparing the article text for modeling by performing text preprocessing techniques such as tokenization, lowercasing, removing stopwords, and stemming or lemmatization. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9740cc4c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Tokenization: Involves splitting the text into individual words/tokens. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "id": "f1c0cbaa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tokenize the article text\n",
    "df['Tokenized Text'] = df['Article Text'].apply(word_tokenize)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f75b5596",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Lowercasing: Converting all the tokens to lowercase to ensure case insensitivity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "id": "19464464",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df['Tokenized Text'] = df['Tokenized Text'].apply(lambda x: [word.lower() for word in x])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9a8e18ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Removing Stopwords: Stopwords are common words that do not carry significant meaning and can be removed from the text."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "id": "cc084f0b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from nltk.corpus import stopwords\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove stopwords\n",
    "stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))\n",
    "df['Filtered Text'] = df['Tokenized Text'].apply(lambda x: [word for word in x if word.lower() not in stop_words])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fe08a5d6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Stemming: Technique used to reduce words to their root form. Stemming reduces words to their base or stem form.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 41,
   "id": "6363d4d7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from nltk.stem import PorterStemmer\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize the stemmer\n",
    "stemmer = PorterStemmer()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply stemming to the filtered text\n",
    "df['Stemmed Text'] = df['Filtered Text'].apply(lambda x: [stemmer.stem(word) for word in x])\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e43ba282",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 3. Feature Extraction: \n",
    "\n",
    "### Using techniques like TF-IDF (Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency) and word embeddings to convert the text into numerical features that can be used for machine learning."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4ea5a11f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> TF-IDF (Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency):\n",
    "TF-IDF is a widely used technique that assigns weights to words based on their frequency in a document and across the entire corpus."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "id": "bbfe41c6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n",
    "\n",
    "# Join the list of preprocessed words into a single string\n",
    "preprocessed_text = df['Stemmed Text'].apply(' '.join)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize the TfidfVectorizer\n",
    "tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit-transform the preprocessed text\n",
    "tfidf_features = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(preprocessed_text)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the feature names from the vectorizer's vocabulary\n",
    "feature_names = tfidf_vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert the TF-IDF features to a DataFrame\n",
    "tfidf_df = pd.DataFrame(tfidf_features.toarray(), columns=feature_names)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "62ab73db",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Word Embeddings (Word2Vec or GloVe):\n",
    "Word embeddings represent words in a continuous vector space, where the vectors capture semantic relationships between words."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 59,
   "id": "a30ca68f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from gensim.models import Word2Vec\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tokenized text from 'Stemmed Text' column\n",
    "tokenized_text = df['Stemmed Text']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train the Word2Vec model\n",
    "word2vec_model = Word2Vec(sentences=tokenized_text, vector_size=100, window=5, min_count=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the word embeddings\n",
    "word_embeddings = word2vec_model.wv\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example usage:\n",
    "# Access the word vector for a specific word\n",
    "vector = word_embeddings['word']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "956af89b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 4. Model Training:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5c728300",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA):\n",
    "LDA is a probabilistic topic modeling technique that assumes each document is a mixture of various topics and each topic is a distribution of words."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 60,
   "id": "f9578d37",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(0, '0.016*\"notam\" + 0.012*\"test\" + 0.011*\".\" + 0.008*\"area\" + 0.008*\"twitter\" + 0.008*\"user\" + 0.008*\"issu\" + 0.008*\"@\" + 0.007*\"period\" + 0.007*\"notic\"')\n",
      "(1, '0.073*\",\" + 0.054*\".\" + 0.016*\"said\" + 0.015*\"â€œ\" + 0.015*\"â€™\" + 0.015*\"â€\" + 0.014*\"india\" + 0.009*\"minist\" + 0.007*\"countri\" + 0.006*\"meet\"')\n",

      "(6, '0.032*\"articl\" + 0.026*\".\" + 0.016*\"inform\" + 0.014*\",\" + 0.013*\"opinion\" + 0.012*\"idrw.org\" + 0.012*\"india\" + 0.009*\"writer\" + 0.008*\"eject\" + 0.008*\"respons\"')\n",
      "(7, '0.047*\"submarin\" + 0.029*\".\" + 0.021*\"navi\" + 0.016*\",\" + 0.015*\"indian\" + 0.014*\"india\" + 0.012*\"nuclear\" + 0.011*\"develop\" + 0.009*\"class\" + 0.009*\")\"')\n",
      "(8, '0.047*\",\" + 0.036*\".\" + 0.015*\"navi\" + 0.013*\"indian\" + 0.012*\"said\" + 0.009*\"oper\" + 0.009*\"maritim\" + 0.009*\")\" + 0.009*\"(\" + 0.008*\"ship\"')\n",
      "(9, '0.044*\",\" + 0.043*\".\" + 0.024*\"(\" + 0.024*\")\" + 0.012*\"/\" + 0.011*\"indian\" + 0.010*\"aircraft\" + 0.008*\"develop\" + 0.007*\":\" + 0.007*\"idrw.org\"')\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from gensim import corpora, models\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a dictionary from the preprocessed text\n",
    "dictionary = corpora.Dictionary(tokenized_text)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert tokenized text to bag-of-words representation\n",
    "corpus = [dictionary.doc2bow(text) for text in tokenized_text]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train the LDA model\n",
    "num_topics = 10  # Specify the number of topics to discover\n",
    "lda_model = models.LdaModel(corpus, num_topics=num_topics, id2word=dictionary, passes=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the topics and their associated words\n",
    "topics = lda_model.print_topics(num_words=10)\n",
    "for topic in topics:\n",
    "    print(topic)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ac9250a4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Non-negative Matrix Factorization (NMF):\n",
    "NMF is a matrix factorization technique that can be used for topic modeling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 62,
   "id": "07e8f55e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Topic #0:\n",
      "['iaf', 'teja', 'aircraft', 'jet', 'fighter', 'hal', 'air', 'lca', 'trainer', 'forc']\n",
      "Topic #1:\n",
      "['modi', 'said', 'prime', 'minist', 'visit', 'india', 'pm', 'summit', 'quad', 'pacif']\n",
      "Topic #2:\n",
      "['missil', 'rang', 'air', 'brahmo', 'cruis', 'notam', 'system', 'test', 'launch', 'ballist']\n",
      "Topic #3:\n",
      "['submarin', 'nuclear', 'navi', 'class', 'india', 'offer', 'attack', 'program', 'indian', 'kalvari']\n",
      "Topic #4:\n",
      "['engin', 'program', 'amca', 'develop', 'ge', 'thrust', 'gener', 'kaveri', 'india', 'f414']\n",
      "Topic #5:\n",
      "['drone', 'system', 'uav', 'armi', 'gun', 'develop', 'tank', 'vehicl', 'indian', 'defenc']\n",
      "Topic #6:\n",
      "['said', 'terrorist', 'polic', 'kashmir', 'jammu', 'armi', 'district', 'area', 'offici', 'secur']\n",
      "Topic #7:\n",
      "['articl', 'opinion', 'inform', 'writer', 'respons', 'take', 'org', 'idrw', 'satyajeet', 'kumar']\n",
      "Topic #8:\n",
      "['navi', 'carrier', 'aircraft', 'indian', 'in', 'deck', 'vikrant', 'ship', 'oper', 'maritim']\n",
      "Topic #9:\n",
      "['sco', 'pakistan', 'foreign', 'minist', 'india', 'meet', 'jaishankar', 'china', 'g20', 'said']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.decomposition import NMF\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create the TF-IDF matrix\n",
    "tfidf_matrix = tfidf_features.toarray()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train the NMF model\n",
    "num_topics = 10  # Specify the number of topics to discover\n",
    "nmf_model = NMF(n_components=num_topics, random_state=42)\n",
    "nmf_model.fit(tfidf_matrix)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the feature names from the vectorizer's vocabulary\n",
    "feature_names = tfidf_vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the topics and their associated words\n",
    "for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(nmf_model.components_):\n",
    "    print(f\"Topic #{topic_idx}:\")\n",
    "    top_words_idx = topic.argsort()[:-10 - 1:-1]\n",
    "    top_words = [feature_names[i] for i in top_words_idx]\n",
    "    print(top_words)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "783dfea5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 5. Interpretation of Results: \n",
    "\n",
    "### Analyzing the outputs from the trained model and extracting meaningful insights from the discovered trends or clusters."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ece146f9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Topic Distribution: Calculating the topic distribution for each document/article and determining the dominant topic and its corresponding probability."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 64,
   "id": "52a18a2c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np \n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the topic distribution for each document\n",
    "topic_distribution = nmf_model.transform(tfidf_matrix)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Determine the dominant topic for each document\n",
    "dominant_topics = np.argmax(topic_distribution, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the corresponding probabilities for the dominant topics\n",
    "dominant_topic_probs = np.max(topic_distribution, axis=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c30c0b7b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Topic Frequency Over Time"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 71,
   "id": "5444d10c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Add a column for the year and month\n",
    "df['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Published Date']).dt.year\n",
    "df['Month'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Published Date']).dt.month\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the topic counts by year and dominant topic\n",
    "topic_counts_by_year = df.groupby(['Year', 'Dominant Topic']).size().reset_index(name='Article Count')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4529bef9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> Topic Co-occurrence: Exploring relationships between different topics by analyzing their co-occurrence patterns."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 72,
   "id": "fd7b24b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate the co-occurrence matrix\n",
    "co_occurrence_matrix = topic_distribution.T.dot(topic_distribution)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute pointwise mutual information (PMI)\n",
    "total_docs = len(df)\n",
    "topic_probs = topic_distribution.sum(axis=0) / total_docs\n",
    "pmi = np.log(co_occurrence_matrix / (topic_probs[:, np.newaxis] * topic_probs))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d434057b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

       "<Figure size 1000x800 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set the number of topics and words to display in the heatmap\n",
    "num_topics_to_display = 10\n",
    "num_words_to_display = 10\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the top words for each topic\n",
    "top_words_per_topic = []\n",
    "for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(nmf_model.components_):\n",
    "    top_words_idx = topic.argsort()[:-num_words_to_display - 1:-1]\n",
    "    top_words = [feature_names[i] for i in top_words_idx]\n",
    "    top_words_per_topic.append(top_words)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a subset of the topic-word matrix\n",
    "topic_word_matrix_subset = topic_word_matrix[:num_words_to_display, :num_topics_to_display]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a list of words and topics to display\n",
    "words_to_display = feature_names[:num_words_to_display]\n",
    "topics_to_display = [f\"Topic {idx+1}: {' '.join(top_words_per_topic[idx])}\" for idx in range(num_topics_to_display)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a heatmap\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(topic_word_matrix_subset.T, cmap='Blues', xticklabels=words_to_display, yticklabels=topics_to_display)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Word')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Topic')\n",
    "plt.title('Topic-Word Matrix')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the topic counts by year and dominant topic\n",
    "topic_counts_by_year = df.groupby(['Year', 'Dominant Topic']).size().reset_index(name='Document Count')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a line chart for each topic\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "for topic in topic_counts_by_year['Dominant Topic'].unique():\n",
    "    topic_data = topic_counts_by_year[topic_counts_by_year['Dominant Topic'] == topic]\n",
    "    plt.plot(topic_data['Year'], topic_data['Document Count'], label=topic)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Year')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Document Count')\n",
    "plt.title('Topic Evolution Over Time')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.legend(title='Topic')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
